    "html": "<div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert dark\"><h3><strong>Binary Semaphore vs. Mutex: Key Differences</strong></h3><p>While both <strong>binary semaphores</strong> and <strong>mutexes</strong> are used for <strong>mutual exclusion</strong>, they have important differences in terms of <strong>ownership, behavior, and use cases</strong>.</p><table><thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th><strong>Binary Semaphore</strong></th><th><strong>Mutex</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Value Range</strong></td><td><code>0</code> or <code>1</code></td><td><code>Locked</code> or <code>Unlocked</code></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Ownership</strong></td><td><strong>No ownership</strong> (any process can <code>signal</code>)</td><td><strong>Has ownership</strong> (only the owner can <code>unlock</code>)</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Blocking Behavior</strong></td><td>Processes are <strong>blocked</strong> when <code>wait(S)</code> is called on <code>S == 0</code></td><td>Thread is <strong>put to sleep</strong> when <code>lock()</code> is called on a locked mutex</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Waking Up</strong></td><td>Any process can <code>signal(S)</code> to unblock another process</td><td>Only the <strong>owner</strong> thread can <code>unlock()</code></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Usage</strong></td><td>Synchronization between <strong>processes and threads</strong></td><td>Mostly used for <strong>thread synchronization</strong></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Priority Inversion Handling</strong></td><td>No built-in handling</td><td>Some mutexes support <strong>priority inheritance</strong></td></tr></tbody></table><hr><h3><strong>1Ô∏è‚É£ Ownership Difference</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Mutex:</strong> The thread that locks a mutex <strong>must be the one to unlock it</strong>.</li><li><strong>Binary Semaphore:</strong> Any process or thread can <strong>signal (<code>V(S)</code>)</strong> to release a blocked process.</li></ul><p>üîπ <strong>Example Issue in Binary Semaphore:</strong><br>Process A acquires <code>wait(S)</code>, but Process B calls <code>signal(S)</code>, which can cause unexpected behavior (incorrectly unblocking a different process).</p><p>üîπ <strong>Example Issue in Mutex:</strong><br>If a thread forgets to unlock a mutex, other threads will be stuck indefinitely.</p><hr><h3><strong>2Ô∏è‚É£ Example Code Comparison</strong></h3><h4><strong>Binary Semaphore: No Ownership</strong></h4><pre class=\"!overflow-visible\"><div class=\"contain-inline-size rounded-md border-[0.5px] border-token-border-medium relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary dark:bg-gray-950\"><div class=\"flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between rounded-t-md h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary dark:bg-token-main-surface-secondary select-none\">cpp</div><div class=\"sticky top-9 md:top-[5.75rem]\"><div class=\"absolute bottom-0 right-2 flex h-9 items-center\"><div class=\"flex items-center rounded bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary px-2 font-sans text-xs text-token-text-secondary dark:bg-token-main-surface-secondary\"><span class=\"\" data-state=\"closed\"><button class=\"flex gap-1 items-center select-none px-4 py-1\" aria-label=\"Copy\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"icon-xs\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M7 5C7 3.34315 8.34315 2 10 2H19C20.6569 2 22 3.34315 22 5V14C22 15.6569 20.6569 17 19 17H17V19C17 20.6569 15.6569 22 14 22H5C3.34315 22 2 20.6569 2 19V10C2 8.34315 3.34315 7 5 7H7V5ZM9 7H14C15.6569 7 17 8.34315 17 10V15H19C19.5523 15 20 14.5523 20 14V5C20 4.44772 19.5523 4 19 4H10C9.44772 4 9 4.44772 9 5V7ZM5 9C4.44772 9 4 9.44772 4 10V19C4 19.5523 4.44772 20 5 20H14C14.5523 20 15 19.5523 15 19V10C15 9.44772 14.5523 9 14 9H5Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path></svg>Copy</button></span><span class=\"\" data-state=\"closed\"><button class=\"flex select-none items-center gap-1\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"icon-xs\"><path d=\"M2.5 5.5C4.3 5.2 5.2 4 5.5 2.5C5.8 4 6.7 5.2 8.5 5.5C6.7 5.8 5.8 7 5.5 8.5C5.2 7 4.3 5.8 2.5 5.5Z\" fill=\"currentColor\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"></path><path d=\"M5.66282 16.5231L5.18413 19.3952C5.12203 19.7678 5.09098 19.9541 5.14876 20.0888C5.19933 20.2067 5.29328 20.3007 5.41118 20.3512C5.54589 20.409 5.73218 20.378 6.10476 20.3159L8.97693 19.8372C9.72813 19.712 10.1037 19.6494 10.4542 19.521C10.7652 19.407 11.0608 19.2549 11.3343 19.068C11.6425 18.8575 11.9118 18.5882 12.4503 18.0497L20 10.5C21.3807 9.11929 21.3807 6.88071 20 5.5C18.6193 4.11929 16.3807 4.11929 15 5.5L7.45026 13.0497C6.91175 13.5882 6.6425 13.8575 6.43197 14.1657C6.24513 14.4392 6.09299 14.7348 5.97903 15.0458C5.85062 15.3963 5.78802 15.7719 5.66282 16.5231Z\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"></path><path d=\"M14.5 7L18.5 11\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"></path></svg>Edit</button></span></div></div></div><div class=\"overflow-y-auto p-4\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"!whitespace-pre language-cpp\"><span>semaphore S = <span class=\"hljs-number\">1</span>;  <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Binary semaphore starts at 1</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-type\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\">process_A</span><span class=\"hljs-params\">()</span> </span>{\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\">wait</span>(S);  <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// If S == 0, process is blocked</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Critical Section</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-built_in\">signal</span>(S);  <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Any process can call signal()</span>\n}\n</span></code></div></div></pre><h4><strong>Mutex: Ownership Required</strong></h4><pre class=\"!overflow-visible\"><div class=\"contain-inline-size rounded-md border-[0.5px] border-token-border-medium relative bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary dark:bg-gray-950\"><div class=\"flex items-center text-token-text-secondary px-4 py-2 text-xs font-sans justify-between rounded-t-md h-9 bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary dark:bg-token-main-surface-secondary select-none\">cpp</div><div class=\"sticky top-9 md:top-[5.75rem]\"><div class=\"absolute bottom-0 right-2 flex h-9 items-center\"><div class=\"flex items-center rounded bg-token-sidebar-surface-primary px-2 font-sans text-xs text-token-text-secondary dark:bg-token-main-surface-secondary\"><span class=\"\" data-state=\"closed\"><button class=\"flex gap-1 items-center select-none px-4 py-1\" aria-label=\"Copy\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"icon-xs\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" clip-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M7 5C7 3.34315 8.34315 2 10 2H19C20.6569 2 22 3.34315 22 5V14C22 15.6569 20.6569 17 19 17H17V19C17 20.6569 15.6569 22 14 22H5C3.34315 22 2 20.6569 2 19V10C2 8.34315 3.34315 7 5 7H7V5ZM9 7H14C15.6569 7 17 8.34315 17 10V15H19C19.5523 15 20 14.5523 20 14V5C20 4.44772 19.5523 4 19 4H10C9.44772 4 9 4.44772 9 5V7ZM5 9C4.44772 9 4 9.44772 4 10V19C4 19.5523 4.44772 20 5 20H14C14.5523 20 15 19.5523 15 19V10C15 9.44772 14.5523 9 14 9H5Z\" fill=\"currentColor\"></path></svg>Copy</button></span><span class=\"\" data-state=\"closed\"><button class=\"flex select-none items-center gap-1\"><svg width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" class=\"icon-xs\"><path d=\"M2.5 5.5C4.3 5.2 5.2 4 5.5 2.5C5.8 4 6.7 5.2 8.5 5.5C6.7 5.8 5.8 7 5.5 8.5C5.2 7 4.3 5.8 2.5 5.5Z\" fill=\"currentColor\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"></path><path d=\"M5.66282 16.5231L5.18413 19.3952C5.12203 19.7678 5.09098 19.9541 5.14876 20.0888C5.19933 20.2067 5.29328 20.3007 5.41118 20.3512C5.54589 20.409 5.73218 20.378 6.10476 20.3159L8.97693 19.8372C9.72813 19.712 10.1037 19.6494 10.4542 19.521C10.7652 19.407 11.0608 19.2549 11.3343 19.068C11.6425 18.8575 11.9118 18.5882 12.4503 18.0497L20 10.5C21.3807 9.11929 21.3807 6.88071 20 5.5C18.6193 4.11929 16.3807 4.11929 15 5.5L7.45026 13.0497C6.91175 13.5882 6.6425 13.8575 6.43197 14.1657C6.24513 14.4392 6.09299 14.7348 5.97903 15.0458C5.85062 15.3963 5.78802 15.7719 5.66282 16.5231Z\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"></path><path d=\"M14.5 7L18.5 11\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\"></path></svg>Edit</button></span></div></div></div><div class=\"overflow-y-auto p-4\" dir=\"ltr\"><code class=\"!whitespace-pre language-cpp\"><span>std::mutex mtx;\n\n<span class=\"hljs-function\"><span class=\"hljs-type\">void</span> <span class=\"hljs-title\">thread_A</span><span class=\"hljs-params\">()</span> </span>{\n    mtx.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\">lock</span>();   <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Thread A locks the mutex</span>\n    <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Critical Section</span>\n    mtx.<span class=\"hljs-built_in\">unlock</span>(); <span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Only Thread A can unlock</span>\n}\n</span></code></div></div></pre><hr><h3><strong>3Ô∏è‚É£ Priority Inversion</strong></h3><ul><li><strong>Binary Semaphore:</strong> Does not handle priority inversion. If a high-priority task is waiting, a lower-priority task might still hold the semaphore.</li><li><strong>Mutex:</strong> Some mutexes (e.g., <strong>priority inheritance mutex</strong>) allow a low-priority thread to temporarily inherit a higher priority to release the lock.</li></ul><hr><h3><strong>4Ô∏è‚É£ Use Cases</strong></h3><table><thead><tr><th>Use Case</th><th><strong>Binary Semaphore</strong></th><th><strong>Mutex</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>Process synchronization</strong> (e.g., producer-consumer)</td><td>‚úÖ Yes</td><td>‚ùå No</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Thread synchronization</strong> (within a single process)</td><td>‚úÖ Yes</td><td>‚úÖ Yes</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Strict mutual exclusion (ownership required)</strong></td><td>‚ùå No</td><td>‚úÖ Yes</td></tr></tbody></table><hr><h3><strong>Final Answer:</strong></h3><p>‚úî <strong>Mutex = Strict ownership (only locker can unlock, used for thread safety).</strong><br>‚úî <strong>Binary Semaphore = No ownership (anyone can signal, used for process and thread sync).</strong><br>‚úî <strong>Mutexes are better for critical sections, while semaphores are better for signaling and resource management.</strong></p><p>Would you like an example of a priority inversion issue and how mutex handles it? üöÄ</p></div>"
